name: Wendell LONG, Petitioner, v. Judge Webster KEOGH, Court of Common Pleas-Trial Division P.C.R.A. Unit, Respondents

parties: Wendell LONG, Petitioner, v. Judge Webster KEOGH, Court of Common Pleas-Trial Division P.C.R.A. Unit, Respondents.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 7th day of February, 2008, the Application for Leave to File Original Process is granted. The Petition for Writ of Mandamus is denied, and the Prothonotary’s Office is directed ,to strike the judge’s name from the caption.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

941 A.2d 1260
Wendell LONG, Petitioner, v. Judge Webster KEOGH, Court of Common Pleas-Trial Division P.C.R.A. Unit, Respondents.
No. 196 EM 2007.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
Feb. 7, 2008.
